cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL

The paper proposes a new activation function for neural networks and evaluates its performance on various benchmark datasets using different types of neural networks. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories such as Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Computation and Language (cs.CL). However, since the focus is on the activation function and its impact on the training and classification performance, cs.NE and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories.
